article.description: — Ken Evans had 17 points to help Jackson State fend off Bethune-Cookman 61-60 on Monday night.
article.headline: Evans helps Jackson State hold off Bethune-Cookman 61-60
article.linkText: Evans helps Jackson State hold off Bethune-Cookman 61-60
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. -- — Ken Evans had 17 points to help Jackson State fend off Bethune-Cookman 61-60 on Monday night. Evans had five rebounds for the Tigers (12-14, 8-5 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Jordan O'Neal scored 16 points and grabbed eight rebounds. Keionte Cornelius made three 3-pointers and scored 11. The Wildcats (12-14, 7-6) were led by Jakobi Heady's 17 points. Dhashon Dyson had 14 points and Zion Harmon scored 13. Jackson State won despite not scoring over the final 3:30 of the game. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
